Introduced Version
SENATE BILL No. 119
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 35-42-4.
Synopsis: Grooming. Adds a facility or event that provides
entertainment or programming primarily directed toward a child less
than 18 years of age to the list of facilities at which a sexually violent
predator or an offender against children may not work or volunteer.
Adds entering a facility or location holding an event that provides
entertainment or programming primarily directed toward a child less
than 18 years of age by a serious sex offender to the crime of unlawful
entry by a serious sex offender. Renames the offense of "inappropriate
communication with a child" to "sexual grooming", and provides (in
addition to the current elements of the offense) that a person commits
the offense if the person engages in a pattern of repeated or continuous
contact with an individual whom the person believes to be a child less
than 14 years of age, with the intent to make the individual less
resistant to future unlawful sexual conduct.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Dernulc
December 9, 2025, read first time and referred to Committee on Corrections and Criminal
Law.
